      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "- Add new commands\r\n\t- `Go to next tab`\r\n\t- `Go to previous tab`\r\n- Add new options for new commands\r\n\t- `Color of button frame on focus`\r\n\t- `Main modifier key`\r\n\t- `Action key`\r\n\t- `Choose how to go to the previous tab`\r\n\t- `Sub modifier key`\r\n\t- `Back action key`\r\n\r\n## How to use new commands\r\n\r\n1. Set up the `Go to next/previous tab` command in the plugin's settings.\r\n\t1. In the default configuration, each command are as follows.\r\n\t\t1. Tab Selector: Go to next tab: `^Tab` or `Ctrl + Tab`\r\n\t\t2. Tab Selector: Go to previous tab: `^⇧Tab` or `Ctrl + Shift + Tab`\r\n\t2. Don't use shortcut keys reserved by the OS. OS shortcut keys take precedence and don't work properly.\r\n\t\t1. In case MacOS, `⌘Tab` and `⌥Tab` etc… can't use.\r\n2. Set hotkeys to match the command settings implemented above.\r\n4. From then on you can switch tabs using hotkeys.\r\n\r\n![demo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/namikaze-40p/obsidian-tab-selector/main/demo/ver-0.5.0/switch-tab-in-history.gif)",
